{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"29f0e8c8-880b-4aa1-b06c-dcaedc8952e2","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~X&Category=Y`) is replaced by MTP's `--filter` syntax. The operators differ:\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `~` (contains) | `~=` |\n| `=` (equals) | `=` |\n| `&` (and) | `&` |\n| `Category` trait | `Category` (same) |\n\n### 2. Your new command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe only change is `~` → `~=` for the contains operator. The `&` and trait name `Category` stay the same.\n\n### If you need to run via the executable directly (MTP native):\n\n```bash\n./TestProject --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### Quick reference of MTP filter operators:\n- `=` exact match\n- `!=` not equal\n- `~=` contains\n- `!~=` does not contain","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51cf5e75-5810-499b-9cc9-0ddaf6e69793","outputTokens":289,"requestId":"A02E:350962:1855D9C:1B7945E:69FE873B"},"id":"9113a2c4-556a-4c3e-873c-4a9584fdecc9","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:00:51.995Z","parentId":"20ae6291-b786-422e-ba81-3b1a7bef52e2"}
